2.01 quais sao 3 metodos de ingesting files from cloud object storage into delta tables?
CREATE TABLE AS (CTAS), COPY INTO, Auto Loader
ingestion from cloud object storage is perfomed using lakeflow connect standard connectors

2.02 como criar uma tabela a partir de um cloud object storage?
CREATE TABLE new_table AS
SELECT *
FROM read_files(
    <path_to_files(s)>,
    format => '<file_type>',
    <other_format_specific_options>
); 

2.03 o que faz a funça read_files() na criaçao de uma tabela delta table a partir de um cloud object storage?
the read_files() function reads files under a provided location and returns the data in tabular form, automatically detects the file format and infers a unified schema across all files.

2.04 quais sao os formatos aceitos dentro da função read_files()?
json, csv, xml, text, binaryfile, parquet, avro and orc

2.05 como criar uma tabela a partir de um cloud object storage usando o COPY INTO (legacy)?
#you can create an empty table without a schema
#you also can explicitly create the table with a schema
CREATE TABLE new_table; 

COPY INTO new_table
FROM '<dir_path>'
FILEFORMAT=<file_type>
FORMAT_OPTIONS(<options>)
COPY_OPTIONS(<options>)

2.06 para que o copy into é ideal? 
COPY INTO is ideal for situations where the cloud storage location is continuosly adding file, since it is a retriable and indempotent operation designed for incremental batch ingestion

2.07 como funciona o COPY INTO em isercoes de dados incrementais?
COPY INTO will skip any files that have already been loaded into the table, and only new files will be ingested.

2.08 quais tipo de arquivos o COPY INTO suporta?
It supports various common file types like parquet, JSON, XML and others.

2.09 o que faz o FROM no COPY INTO?
the FROM clause specifies the path of the cloud storage location where new files are being continuosly added.

2.10 o que faz o FORMAT_OPTIONS() no COPY INTO?
controls how the source files are parsed and interpreted, and the available options will depend on the file format you're working with.

2.11 o que faz o COPY_OPTIONS() no COPY INTO?
COPY_OPTIONS() let you control the behavior of the COPY INTO operation itself. For example, options like schema evolution using mergeSchema, or idempotency using force. 

2.12 quais linguagem o auto loader tem suporte?
python and sql

2.13 em casos de uso qual é o melhor metodo de ingestion type para processar milhoes de files? Auto loader, create table as, copy into?
auto loader

2.14 sobre qual tecnologia o auto loader é construido?
spark structured streaming

2.15 o que é o auto loader e quais beneficios ele contem?
auto loader incrementally and efficiently processes new data files in either in batch or streaming mode as they arrive in cloud storage, and it does this without any additional setup. You can also use Auto loader, which is a feature that automatically detects and ingests new files from cloud storage into delta lake table, simplifying the process of handling incrmental or streming data with minimal configuration.

2.16 com fazemos um incremental data ingestion com python auto loader?
spark
.readStrem
    .format("cloudFiles")
    .option("cloudFiles.format", "json")
    .option("cloudFiles.schemaLocation", "<checkpoint_path>")
    .load("/Volumes/catalog/schema/files")
.writeStream
    .option("checkpointLocation", "<checkpoint_path>")
    .trigger(processingTime="5 seconds")
    .toTable("catalog.database.table")

2.17 o que faz o .load() quando usamos o auto loader?
we use .load() to point to the location of the files, in this case a path under /Volumes referencing Unity Catalog.

2.18 quando estamos usando o .writeStrem como fazemos para saber o estado e progresso, e ter um intervalo de escrita?
we configure .writeStrem  with a checkpoint location to maintain state and progress and set a trigger .trigger() interval of every 5 seconds.

2.19 o que faz o .toTabel() no autoLoader?
we use .toTable() to write the data into a delta table specified by catalog, database, and table name.


